cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.MM, cs.IR, cs.LG 

This paper deals with learning visual-semantic embeddings for cross-modal retrieval, which involves computer vision (CV) and natural language processing (NLP) tasks. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves multi-modal learning, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia). The use of ranking loss functions and structured prediction also suggests the possibility of cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-categories.
